 :tx/rationale "STRUCTURAL ANALYSIS: What does 'forced to search first' mean? The CRB gate (INV-GUIDANCE-025) already exists as a concept — when reconciliation finds 3+ matches, the command requires --reconciled flag. But the CRB gate runs on the OUTPUT text of the command (the observation body, the task title). It does NOT run on the INTENT that precedes the command. The agent's reasoning goes: (1) I have an idea → (2) I formulate it as a task → (3) braid task create runs CRB on the FORMULATED text → (4) CRB finds or doesn't find matches. The problem: step 3 runs CRB on the FULL TITLE (500 chars of BACKGROUND) which dilutes the signal. TAP-SPLIT fixes this by making the title short. But there's a deeper issue: CRB runs AFTER the agent has already committed cognitive effort to formulating the task. Sunk cost bias makes the agent want to proceed even when matches are found. The maximally structural solution: CRB should run at INTENT time, not at COMMAND time. When the agent THINKS about creating a task (before typing the command), the system should already be showing related work. This is exactly what the Ambient Reconciliation concentration detector does — it surfaces related work through braid status BEFORE the agent creates anything. The two systems compose: AR concentration prevents the agent from entering a neighborhood without seeing what's there. CRB gate prevents the agent from creating in a neighborhood without reconciling. Together they form a two-layer defense: awareness (AR) + enforcement (CRB)."
